narrative.domain_description:
[p]The domain represented by this model is a business environment focused on sales and distribution of cycling-related products. Key people include customers, salespersons, and company representatives. Customers can have multiple addresses and place orders, which are managed by salespersons. Places in this domain are customer addresses, company locations, and shipping destinations. Products are categorized and described in detail, with each having a model and description that ties back to the product's features and specifications. [/p]

[p]Interactions occur through the placement and fulfillment of sales orders. Customers interact with salespersons to purchase products, which are then shipped to specified addresses. Products are organized into categories and models, each with specific descriptions and attributes like color, size, and cost. The domain operates under logical rules where each customer can have multiple orders and addresses, and each product can be part of multiple sales orders. Insights reveal a structured system where product details and customer information are crucial for efficient operations. [/p]

narrative.what_is: [p]A Customer in this domain is an entity, often a business, that purchases cycling-related products from the company. Customers have unique identifiers and can be associated with multiple addresses and orders. They interact with salespersons to place orders, which are then processed and fulfilled by the company. Each customer has contact details, including email and phone numbers, and may represent a company or individual.[/p]

interact_with_other.people: [p]Customers primarily interact with salespersons who assist them in selecting and purchasing products. Salespersons manage customer accounts and ensure that orders are processed efficiently. Customers may also communicate with company representatives for support or inquiries about products and services.[/p]
interact_with_other.places: [p]Customers are linked to various places, such as their business addresses and shipping destinations. These locations are crucial for order fulfillment, as products are dispatched to these addresses. Customers may have multiple addresses, allowing for flexibility in shipping and billing.[/p]
interact_with_other.things: [p]Customers interact with products by placing orders for items that meet their needs. They select products based on specifications like size, color, and cost. The interaction with products is facilitated through sales orders, which detail the items purchased and their quantities.[/p]

narrative.what_is: [p]A ProductModel is a specific version or design of a cycling-related product within a business environment focused on sales and distribution. It serves as a blueprint for various products, each having distinct features such as color, size, and specifications. ProductModels are essential for organizing products into categories and ensuring that each product meets the required standards and descriptions. They help streamline the sales process by providing detailed information about the products, which is crucial for both salespersons and customers. [/p]

interact_with_other.people: [p]ProductModels interact with people primarily through salespersons and customers. Salespersons use ProductModels to understand product specifications and to assist customers in making informed purchasing decisions. Customers rely on these models to compare different products and choose the one that best fits their needs. ProductModels also facilitate communication between company representatives and customers by providing detailed product information.[/p]
interact_with_other.places: [p]ProductModels interact with places by being associated with specific customer addresses, company locations, and shipping destinations. They play a role in determining the logistics of how products are distributed and delivered. The models ensure that products are shipped to the correct locations, adhering to the specifications and requirements outlined in the sales orders.[/p]
interact_with_other.things: [p]ProductModels interact with other things by being linked to various products and sales orders. Each ProductModel can have multiple products associated with it, each with unique attributes like color and size. They are integral to the organization of sales orders, ensuring that each order is fulfilled accurately according to the product specifications. ProductModels also connect with product descriptions, providing a comprehensive overview of the product's features and benefits.[/p]

properties.description: This property indicates the name of the product design, helping to identify the specific design associated with a product in a sales order.

properties.name: CatalogDescription
properties.title: catalog description
properties.description: This property provides a description from the catalog, offering additional details about the product design for reference in sales orders.

properties.name: ModifiedDate
properties.title: modified date
properties.description: This property records the date when the product design was last modified, ensuring that the most current version is referenced in sales orders.
